(Sorry I didn't get back sooner)

(Responding to all posts)
Lunarpine looked up at Shadow Wing, "No thanks, I've already eaten," he says
glancing behind a nearby rock where the remains of an antelope lay, it'd
been a while since the kill, insects were already takeing care of the
leftovers.

"I'm glad you found me." he rolled over exposing his vulnerable side."Take
your best shot, I deserve it for how I treated you."

He paused waiting for her response.
"I didn't mean that you couldn't fight at my side, I just meant that there
were other bots needing your help more." He was trying to choose his words
wisely to avoid sticking another paw in his mouth. "I'm a wolf, my sense of
smells better than most bots sight. Even if I didn't have my scanners, multi
vision sensors or any sight at all I'm still a better warrior than nearly
anyone there.

He paused again, he didn't want her to know about his defect."You and Prowl
put to much thought on me and put yourself at risk and look what happened,
both of you went down protecting me when I could have moved better if I
wasn't worrying about you. A unit needs to know the strengths and weaknesses
of each member, without that their just getting in eachothers way. We won
the fight, we were lucky."

"Oh I almost forgot, thanks for saving me.".
